reviews.text:
Every time I‚Äôm back in Wanaque visiting family, Luigi‚Äôs is a must-stop - and this visit marked my fourth time here in the last three years. It‚Äôs one of my favorite places to eat whenever I‚Äôm in town.

From the moment you walk in, there‚Äôs a sense of warmth and community. The wall of children‚Äôs drawings, the friendly counter staff, and the nostalgic charm of the space make it feel like home. And the food? Absolutely outstanding. The pepperoni and black olive pizza I had today was perfect - crispy crust, generous toppings, and just the right amount of cheese and sauce.

Luigi‚Äôs is a local gem that captures everything you want in a classic neighborhood pizzeria: quality ingredients, consistency, and heart. It‚Äôs no surprise they‚Äôve been serving the community since 1968 - they‚Äôve clearly got something special.

Whether you‚Äôre a local or just passing through, do yourself a favor and grab a slice (or a whole pie). You‚Äôll see why it‚Äôs always on my list when I‚Äôm in Wanaque.

Hands down the best grandma pizza I've ever had. My grandparents live a few minutes away from this place and we always come here. The vodka sauce and pizza are extremely good, and I've always loved their calamari as well. Their fried doughnuts are also good!

I've been eating Luigi's pizza since 1968, when they were located at the Geppetto location on Ringwood Ave.
Still my benchmark for the best pizza üçï and authentic Italian entrees. Worth every dollar!
They have so many loyal customers that they overnight pizza across the country.
I now live over 80 miles away, but it's still worth the trip. Thank you Luigi and sons. It's always nice to see you.

Ordered a pie. After 40mins called just ro ask if it was on its way. Got told "its only been 40mins it's coming" 20mins later it finally arrives. An hour later. Ice cold. And a side of attitude. New owners suck. Never ordering here again.

Oh. And if you see this dude, it takes more than just a gallon of salt to season vodka sauce.

If you are going to make Uber Eats money, and CHARGE me for a scoop of vodka sauce, dont scree it up and rob me twice.

Pathetic

Whether eating in or taking out, lunch or dinner never disappoints. The staff is always friendly and willing to go the extra mile to make my experience a good one. We ordered Pasta Fagiole and garlic knots to go with the salad and salmon I was making. We ordered extra soup for another night, too. I love Luigi‚Äôs Pasta Fagiole. The tasty broth is thick and it‚Äôs filled with pasta and beans. Very hardy!! The garlic knots satisfied this garlic lover‚Äôs palate. My bread lover son was ecstatic.

We have ordered numerous items from Luigi‚Äôs through the years. They‚Äôre always trying new recipes. Check out their monthly specials. Thank you, Luigi‚Äôs staff,  for always making ordering from you  a delightful experience!
